":0},"title":"Hadith on Quran: Recite and ascend the levels of Paradise","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 16, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Amr reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cIt will be said to the companion of the Quran: Recite and ascend as you recited in the world! Verily, your rank is determined by the last verse you recite.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 2914 Grade: Sahih (authentic)\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":40261,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/05\/29\/listening-reciting-ayah\/","url_meta":{"origin":40259,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Quran: Reward for listening and reciting a verse","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 29, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever listens to a verse from the Book of Allah Almighty will have a multiplied reward. Whoever recites a verse will have a light on the Day of Resurrection.\u201d Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 8494 Grade: Hasan (fair)\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":23849,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/10\/05\/ibn-masud-tawbah-zina\/","url_meta":{"origin":40259,"position":2},"title":"Ibn Mas\u2019ud on Tawbah: Allah accepts repentance for adultery, fornication","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 5, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"'Alqamah reported: Abdullah Ibn Mas\u2019ud, may Allah be pleased with him, was asked about a man who has illicit intercourse with a woman and then marries her. Abdullah recited the verse, \u201cThose who do evil deeds and thereafter repent and have faith, your Lord after that is forgiving and merciful.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":14230,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/05\/16\/one-harf-ten-hasanat\/","url_meta":{"origin":40259,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Quran: Single recited letter is ten good deeds","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 16, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever recites a letter from the Book of Allah, he will receive one good deed as ten good deeds like it. I do not say that Alif Lam Mim is one letter, but rather Alif\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15946,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/09\/05\/ayat-al-kursi-greatest-verse\/","url_meta":{"origin":40259,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Ayat al-Kursi: Throne Verse is greatest in Quran","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 5, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Ubayy ibn Ka\u2019b reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cO Abu Mundhir, do you know which verse in the Book of Allah with you is greatest?\u201d I recited, \u201cAllah! There is no God worthy of worship except Him, the Ever-Living, All-Sustaining,\u201d (2:255). The Prophet\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":26486,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/06\/06\/ahl-quran-ahl-allah\/","url_meta":{"origin":40259,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Quran: People of Allah&#8217;s Book are His chosen","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 6, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, Allah has His own people among humanity.\u201d They said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, who are they?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cThey are the people of the Quran, the people of Allah and His chosen ones.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/40259","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2